hesive capsulitis)"}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-secondary mb-4","children":"Recovery & Rehabilitation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed","children":"Post-operative rehabilitation is structured into phases — pain control and range of motion in early weeks, followed by progressive strengthening and sport-specific conditioning. Throwing athletes typically require 4–6 months before returning to competitive play."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-secondary mb-6","children":"Frequently Asked Questions"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","$L9","What is shoulder arthroscopy used for?",{"children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-secondary mb-2 text-base","children":"What is shoulder arthroscopy used for?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-neutral-700 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"Shoulder arthroscopy treats rotator cuff tears, shoulder impingement, labral tears, shoulder instability (Bankart lesions), and frozen shoulder."}]]}],["$","$L9","How long does recovery take after shoulder arthroscopy?",{"children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-secondary mb-2 text-base","children":"How long does recovery take after shoulder arthroscopy?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-neutral-700 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"Recovery depends on the procedure. Impingement decompression may take 4–6 weeks. Rotator cuff repair typically requires 4–6 months for full recovery."}]]}],["$","$L9","Can I avoid shoulder surgery?",{"children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-secondary mb-2 text-base","children":"Can I avoid shoulder surgery?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-neutral-700 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"Many shoulder conditions can be managed non-surgically with physiotherapy, activity modification, and injections. Surgery is recommended when conservative treatment fails or for complete tears."}]]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","aside",null,{"className":"space-y-6","children":[["$","$L9",null,{"children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-heading font-semibold text-secondary mb-4","children":"Book a Consultation"}],["$","$L6",null,{"href":"/contact","className":"block w-full text-center btn-primary","children":"Book Appointment"}],["$","a",null,{"href":"tel:+919145517171","className":"flex items-center justify-center gap-2 mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-600 hover:text-primary transition-colors","children":[["$","svg",null,{"ref":"$undefined","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-phone w-4 h-4","children":[["$","path","foiqr5",{"d":"M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07 19.5 19.5 0 0 1-6-6 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 4.11 2h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 .7 2.81 2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L8.09 9.91a16 16 0 0 0 6 6l1.27-1.27a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 22 16.92z"}],"$undefined"]}]," 9145517171"]}]]}],["$","$L9",null,{"children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-heading font-semibold text-secondary mb-4","children":"Related"}],["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","li","/sports-injuries/gym-shoulder-injuries",{"children":["$","$L6",null,{"href":"/sports-injuries/gym-shoulder-injuries","className":"flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 hover:text-primary transition-colors","children":[["$","svg",null,{"ref":"$undefined","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-chevron-right w-4 h-4 text-primary","children":[["$","path","mthhwq",{"d":"m9 18 6-6-6-6"}],"$undefined"]}]," ","Gym Shoulder Injuries"]}]}],["$","li","/sports-injuries/cricket-injuries",{"ch